# Normalize line endings so every working tree — on every platform — matches
# what is stored in the repository. Without this, git falls back to each
# client's core.autocrlf, and a Windows checkout rewrites LF files to CRLF.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Test fixtures and the tracked sample logs are DATA: their exact bytes,
# line endings included, are what the tests and the walkthrough exercise.
# Never convert them in either direction. This also keeps it possible to add
# a deliberately-CRLF fixture later without it being silently normalized.
tests/fixtures/** -text
sample_logs/** -text

# Binary assets: these contain CR bytes as payload and must never be touched.
*.png binary
*.gif binary
